#Text=Students protest against police action in Jadavpur
#Text=University , Kolkata
#Text=Friday , September 19 , 2014
#Text=35 students of Jadavpur University , Kolkata , India protesting against an August 28 sexual assault case in the university , were arrested by police in the early morning of Wednesday .
#Text=The arrests and alleged baton charge on students led to further protests on Wednesday , including a rally attended by around 3500 people in the evening .

#Text=The protesting students demanded a fresh probe into a molestation incident in which a female student of the university was allegedly sexually abused by male university students who had dragged her to a men 's hostel .
#Text=The students ' gheraoed ' — encircled — the vice-chancellor , Abhijit Chakrabarti , over the incident , demanding a new probe committee be set up and the internal probe committee be dissolved .
#Text=According to students , the current internal probe committee include people who they alleged ' harassed the victim ' .
#Text=The gherao continued for about ten hours by Chakrabarti 's account , preventing the vice-chancellor and the registrar from leaving the campus .
#Text=Students claim they were peacefully protesting and that they had not obstructed any official .
#Text=At around 2am local time ( 0730 UTC ) on Wednesday , police escorted Chakrabarti from the Aurobindo Bhavan administrative building of the university .

#Text=According to Chakrabarti , he " was forced to call police " as he " would have died at [ the protesters ' ] hands had the police not come " ; after escorting him out , they arrested 35 students from the campus , including one female student .
#Text=Police said they later released all the arrested students on personal bond .
#Text=Students allege police turned the lights off and assaulted them , dragging them and charging them with batons .
#Text=They also state there were very few women police , and male officers assaulted female students .
#Text=At least three students were confirmed to have been admitted to the nearby KPC Medical College and Hospital with pain .
#Text=The students lodged a complaint against certain university and police officials , including Chakrabarti and Additional Commissioner of Police Debasish Roy , on Wednesday morning .
#Text=The complaint alleged " goons from a reputed political party walked over bodies of the women after switching the lights off " .
#Text=Police deny the students ' allegations , claiming there were about 40 female police officers , and that students had not been manhandled or assaulted .

#Text=State education minister Partha Chatterjee , of the West Bengal ruling Trinamool Congress party , " condemned " the agitation , suggesting students " were trying to create trouble on the campus .

#Text=The vice-chancellor stated the students damaged the lights in the campus and he  saw students trying to attack me " when police escorted him out of the building .

column1: #Text=In protest of the alleged police assault , a rally was organized for 4pm on Wednesday , beginning from the campus and ending at Golpark .
#Text=Around 3500 people participated in the rally , including students from other colleges and universities of the city .
#Text=Actor-director Koushik Sen and painter Samir Aich were also present in the rally .
#Text=Students of Jadavpur University have decided to indefinitely boycott classes starting from Wednesday .
#Text=They demand the vice-chancellor 's apology and resignation or removal , and the state education minister 's explanation .
#Text=Protests continued on Thursday with certain student unions calling for a student 's strike , by all college and Class X to XII students .
